### GET CLASSES
## Returns a list of classes. The result set is scoped to the authenticated user's role:
##   - Student -> only the class the student belongs to
##   - Teacher -> all classes the teacher is responsible for
##   - Local Admin -> all classes within the admin's school
##   - Admin -> all classes across all schools
##
## Response Body (200 OK) - Array of class objects, each containing:
##   - class_name         (string): Full name of the class (e.g. "26dW")
##   - class_abbreviation (string): Short identifier (e.g. "1dW")
##   - teacher_first_name (string): First name of the responsible teacher
##   - teacher_last_name  (string): Last name of the responsible teacher
##   - teacher_email      (string): Email address of the responsible teacher
##   - persons            (array): List of students in the class, each with:
##       - first_name (string): Student's first name
##       - last_name  (string): Student's last name
##       - email      (string): Student's email address
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - Returns array of GetClassResponse objects
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
GET {{BASE}}/class
Accept: application/json


### CREATE A CLASS
## Creates a new class within the authenticated user's school.
## Restricted to Local Admin or Admin roles.
##
## Request Body:
##   - name         (string, required): Full class name (e.g. "26dW")
##   - abbreviation (string, required): Short class identifier (e.g. "1dW")
##   - description  (string, required): Human-readable description of the class
##   - teacher      (UUID, required): UUID of the teacher responsible for this class
##   - school_id    (UUID, optional): UUID of the school; only necessary if a admin creates a class
##
## Responses:
##   200  OK - Class created successfully
##   400 Bad Request - Missing required fields or invalid UUID format
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
POST {{BASE}}/class
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "name": "26dW",
    "abbreviation": "1dW",
    "description": "Klasse dW im Schuljahr 2025",
    "teacher": "bd102928-e213-4911-8c4d-bf2123addeb8"
}


### EDIT A CLASS
## Partially updates an existing class identified by its UUID in the path.
## Only the fields provided in the request body will be updated (PATCH semantics).
## Restricted to Local Admin or Admin roles.
##
## Path Parameter:
##   - {class_id} (UUID): The UUID of the class to update
##
## Request Body (all fields optional - only included fields are updated):
##   - name         (string, optional): New full class name
##   - abbreviation (string, optional): New short class identifier
##   - description  (string, optional): New description text
##   - teacher      (UUID, optional): UUID of the newly responsible teacher
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - Class updated successfully; returns updated class object
##   400 Bad Request - Invalid UUID format or malformed body
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
PATCH {{BASE}}/class/932f851b-a42f-4653-9c41-d6afd7f771a3
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "description": "Klasse dW im Schuljahr 2026"
}


### DELETE A CLASS
## Permanently deletes a class identified by its UUID in the path.
## This action is irreversible.
## Restricted to Local Admin or Admin roles.
##
## Path Parameter:
##   - {class_id} (UUID): The UUID of the class to delete
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - Class deleted successfully
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
DELETE {{BASE}}/class/932f851b-a42f-4653-9c41-d6afd7f771a3
Accept: application/json
